reviews.comments: Lashes look great but it does smear onto my upper eyelid

reviews.headline: my favourite masacara
reviews.comments:
I used to be a diehard fan of the too faced better than sex mascara and then I tried this one. The other mascara was too dramatic and clumpy. I prefer a softer, more natural type of last look. 

By doing a light coat, I get beautiful definition and length without it looking clumpy or like im wearing a ton of mascara. This is often the only makeup item I will use.

reviews.headline: Too wet!
reviews.comments: Got this for the first time as I've been using the OG one for yearssss but Ulta was out so i saw this one and gave it a shot. Doesn't make lashes as long and the formula is sooooooo wet it will make you look like you sweat or cried after just a couple hours so I'll be going back to the orginal once again :)

reviews.headline: My Year Long Top Mascara
reviews.comments: I love and will always recommend this mascara! It gives the length and definition I need to make my eyes pop. The wand is a personal favorite and the thin brush works to prevent lesser clumps.

reviews.headline: My favorite since 8th grade
reviews.comments: This mascara has seen the ups and downs of my whole highschool career, and I still am in love with the way it makes my lashes look. only complaint (the reason I'm buying a new tube right now) is that the wand itself is quite flimsy and it's hanging by a thread at the moment.

reviews.headline: Good length but so wet
reviews.comments: I apply one thin coat of this mascara and it takes im not even kidding 10 minutes to dry. It gives good length but why is the formula so wet?? The other loreal mascaras are like this too but not this bad.

reviews.headline: Literally my fav mascara
reviews.comments: This by far is the best mascara ever! If you want your lashes to have volume and style I would 100% recommend this product. Take it from someone who gets styes all the time when I use certain mascaras. I literally have used this 4 times and still each time I did not get any styes. Plus it does not itch my eyes either. It gives off that fake lash cat eye kind of look when you use this. And the brush wand is amazing.

reviews.headline: No!
reviews.comments: So clumpy. I have to use a lash brush to separate lashes before it dries or I look like a cartoon character. 0/10

I've tried every method to "gently" remove this mascara, and I was losing a lash or two everytime. I have oil skin and typically does not have a smudging problem with most mascara that I've used in the past. This mascara snudge badddd under my eyes. 1/10 because it did made my lashes look a bit longer.

reviews.headline: Effective but not worth the difficulty removing
reviews.comments: I had no problems with wear or performance, and it looked great as a mascara. But i have sensitive skin and the removal takes so long and i end up loosing so many lashes. I use a cleansing balm and have not had this problem with other mascaras. I would wear if it wasnt so hard to get off.

reviews.headline: Love this mascara
reviews.comments: The applicator is perfect for my short lashes. Doesn't flake off. Goes on easy and defines my lashes with a natural, full look.
